  "about.body.b1": "DialogR is a desktop application for statistical analysis built on top of R. It combines guided, dialog-driven procedures with a live R console, a script editor, a workspace pane, and a data editor, making it possible to move seamlessly between point-and-click analysis and direct scripting in R.",
  "about.body.b2": "It is designed as an incipient alternative to traditional statistical packages such as SPSS, while keeping users close to the actual R syntax and objects that power the analysis.",
  "about.highlights.h1": "Connects directly to the R runtime and keeps the analytical workflow close to real R syntax.",
  "about.highlights.h2": "Provides dialogs for common statistical procedures and data preparation tasks.",
  "about.highlights.h3": "Encourages transparent, reproducible workflows by building R commands with every click.",
